Package org.cloudgraph.recognizer

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GraphRecognizerContext
    Context which supports the evaluation or "recognition" of a given data graph by a binary expression tree, within the context of the expression syntax.
    GraphRecognizerDetector
    A simple query expression visitor which determines whether a graph recognizer is required, within the context of a binary (query) expression syntax tree, encapsulating operator precedence and other factors.
    GraphRecognizerRelationalBinaryExpr
    An RelationalBinaryExpr implementation which uses a specific evaluation context to evaluate the value(s) of a data graph property along the query property traversal path within the context of a binary expression (syntax) tree.
    GraphRecognizerSupport
    Delegate for graph recognizer expression classes.
    GraphRecognizerSyntaxTreeAssembler
    A binary expression tree assembler which constructs an operator precedence map, then visits (traverses) the given predicate expression syntax tree depth-first using an adapted shunting-yard algorithm and assembles a resulting binary tree structure with expression nodes specific for detecting i.e. recognizing a data graph.
    GraphRecognizerWildcardBinaryExpr
    An WildcardBinaryExpr implementation which uses a specific evaluation context to evaluate the value(s) of a data graph property along the query property traversal path within the context of a binary expression (syntax) tree.
